The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Captains for AIDS awareness

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Team India captain Sourav Ganguly and his South African counterpart Graeme Smith joined hands with captains of seven other Test playing nations to lend support to the fight against HIV/AIDS on the occasion of World AIDS Day on Wednesday. 

Sourav and Smith, alongwith members of both teams participating in the second and final Test at the Eden, wore red ribbons to express solidarity to the cause. Even match officials joined in. 

